               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18140216-92-person873">
                  JOHN 
                  THOMAS OXENHAM
               <interp inst="t18140216-92-person873" type="surname" value="THOMAS OXENHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18140216-92-person873" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18140216-92-person873" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18140216-92-viclabel519" type="occupation">patent mangle-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18140216-92-victim872 t18140216-92-viclabel519"></join>, <placeName id="t18140216-92-crimeloc520">354, Oxford-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18140216-92-crimeloc520" type="placeName" value="354, Oxford-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18140216-92-crimeloc520" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18140216-92-off517 t18140216-92-crimeloc520"></join>. I lost my coat about the 10th of January, and the handkerchief out of my bed-room. On the 27th of January, the prisoner was detected in a petty theft. He was my errand-boy. He was detected of taking something out of the cupboard in the kitchen, which was found upon him. It was about eight o'clock in the morning, and when the meat and butter was found in his possession I was called down. I accused him of taking these things; he acknowledged it. I went to Marlborough-street office; I then went with the officer to his mother's apartment; we there found the spoons, the coat, and a silk handkerchief.</p>
               <p>Q. What age is he - A. Eighteen or nineteen. He has been with me six years. Until we discovered this robbery he behaved with the greatest propriety; he was a very industrious, civil, quiet, lad. I would not have prosecuted him if I had not been bound over. I would take him again now; I know he would not be guilty of the like offence.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18140216-92-person874">
                  JOHN 
                  JEFFERIES
               <interp inst="t18140216-92-person874" type="surname" value="JEFFERIES"></interp>
